radiographic_examinations.findings: Partially imaged lung bases are notable for mild dependent atelectasis. No pleural effusion. The liver enhances homogeneously without concerning lesions or biliary dilatation. Gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands are within normal limits. Kidneys enhance and excrete symmetrically without concerning lesions or hydronephrosis. A 4 mm right renal hypodensity is too small to characterize. Stomach is distended with oral contrast. Fluid distended loops of small bowel are normal in course and caliber. No obstruction. Colon is unremarkable. The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated to 9 mm with adjacent fat stranding. No extraluminal gas or large fluid collection to suggest perforation. No intra-abdominal free air or fluid. No mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy. Abdominal aorta is of normal caliber throughout. Bladder is collapsed around a Foley catheter. Uterus is grossly unremarkable. A corpus luteal cyst is incidentally noted in the right ovary. Small amount of pelvic free fluid is present. No concerning lytic or sclerotic osseous lesion identified. Mild sacroiliac degenerative joint disease is present.
